<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/93> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #93" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Listed by Dion. Hal. (8.22.4-5) in the first embassy, composed entirely of consulars, to Coriolanus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/88> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #88" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Dion. Hal. 7.68.1; Chr. 354 (Cornuto et Labo II); Fast. Hyd. (Camerino et Fabio); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); omitted by Livy; Degrassi 88, 354f. On this year, see Dion. Hal. 7.68.1-73.5; Liv. 2.36.1-37.9; Plut. Cor. 24.1-26.3." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/87> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #87" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The notices in Dion. Hal. and Chr. 354 that this was Larcius' second consulship are important in establishing his name, which appears in Dion. Hal. as {Gr}. To this year Dionysius attributes the celebration of the Ludi Magni and the episode of Latinius, which is described in Livy 2.36-37 and Plutarch Cor. 24-26." .
